title: Despite Wins, Saints Drop From NSCAA Poll
text:
Despite Wins, Saints Drop From NSCAA Poll 
By Zach Schneider Despite Wins, Saints Drop From NSCAA Poll   1:24 PM CDT 
Duluth, MN (NNCNOW.com) --- The St. Scholastica men's soccer team dropped from No. 23 to just receiving a single vote in this week's National Soccer Coaches' Association of America (NSCAA) Division III poll, which was released on Tuesday afternoon. 
The Saints went (2-0-1) this past week, including a 3-1 win over Twin Ports rival UW-Superior and a 1-1 draw with Carleton. 
For full results of this week's NSCAA Division III poll, click TEXT GOES HERE 
St. Scholastica is (13-2-1) overall this 2015 season.
